snippet.textDisplay: When a site tells me to stop blocking ads I say, "Well, I guess I don't want to see your shit site, buh bye!" And if I am forced even further to be advertised to, like Yahoo tries to do to me after two decades of not forcing their ad-shit on me...well I will just shut down for good and go back to reading books all the time. I'm old enough I can actually remember a time before computers and smart-phones were a household norm. Life was just fine and we always found plenty to do. I don't mind unobtrusive ads, but the shit you let loose on some websites is ludicrous! The problem is that if more people actually stood up and said NO they would have no choice but to stop, but way too many people don't give a shit, so here we are living Orwell's 1984.
